wsj_2368	45-1	139-155	nce: "Haole" (white) is not the ultimate insult; "Mainland haole" is. Richard Chamberlain dresses as a "Mainland haole," tucking in a Hawaiian shirt and rolling up its long sleeves. And the local expression for brother is "brah," not "bruddah." And even if a nurse would wear flowers in her hair while on duty, if she were engaged she would know to wear them behind her left, not right, ear. Sorry, 	e show does not even have the one redeeming quality of genuine local color. Anita D	_	_	_	_	1>2	Expansion.Restatement.Generalization	Expansion.Restatement.Generalization
